    • Method Detail

      • parseProgram

        protected AbstractSyntaxNode parseProgram()
        Description copied from class: AbstractTableParser
        Parses the table and creates an abstract syntax tree. This is implementation dependend, but should be done in an LL(1) fashion if possible. It is unclear to us if our understanding of a table driven parser would work for LL(2) or any other types of parsers. Therefore, this method would allow the programmer to expirement with a language grammar and try it out! NOTE: This method should not be called more than once.
        Specified by:
        parseProgram in class AbstractTableParser<KleinScanner,KleinToken,KleinParseTable>
        Returns:
        The program tree.
